<br>
Heh...  Its not that Verant didn't consider TLC.  Moreso that they didn't consider anything.  Remember they had planned to have TLC on SOL until whatever flash of insight hit them and they did and decided to poll the players.  How far along were they into SOL development when they polled?  The sad thing is that they had probably already designed these quests and decided to poll when they realised how &quot;nerfed&quot; many quests actually were with TLC.  This is what is scary, Verant originaly intended to have TLC on Luclin and yet they still could not &quot;fix&quot; the quests to work properly.<br>
<br>
As for the arguments about TLC...  Verant decided to make FV the &quot;most difficult server&quot; instead of the roleplaying server.  As someone else said, people come to FV for many reasons, because it is so different from normal servers.  This has ticked off people that wanted a 'roleplaying server' without the added dificulty.  <br>
<br>
All I can say is that they were warned beforehand,though they did at least listen, though not agree.  When they anounced the rules for a roleplaying server (on gameplay, back before they had even anounced Luclin) I argued with Aradune on the messageboard about the &quot;RPness&quot; of TLC.  As well as many of the other features. <br>
<br>
Most of their ruleset I agreed with to a point.  I told them however that while most of their rules were not disagreeable, they were not roleplay related.  I then focused on two issues.<br>
 1. They needed to open another single character server.  Otherwise the server would likely be filled with people looking to that option.  And I pointed out that just because someone hates &quot;twinks&quot; doesn't mean they are a roleplayer.  (I am very glad that Sullon Zek opened with 1 character before FV.  PvP or not I believe it helped in this respect.)<br>
2.  That Warrens Loot Code did nothing to foster roleplay.  Instead it made it more difficult for players with one account to gain items while those with multiple accounts  could still farm to their hearts content.  I then stated that I would play on it, Warren's Loot Code or not... but that it was in no way a &quot;roleplaying rule&quot;.<br>
<br>
I don't recall everything that was said, Aradune responded to comments I made several times on the same thread.  One of Aradune's responses was that it was not intended to be an anti-farming rule but rather it was &quot;roleplay enforcement&quot; because it kept higher level characters out of lower level dungeons.  I remember now that I must have offended him because I said that was gibberish, or rubbish, or something.  And said, if farming isn't an issue what is the problem:  Afterall it was natural for a powerful character to occaisionaly slaughter lesser monsters  (it happens in fantasy fiction, fantasy games, why not EverQuest it is afterall a multiplayer fantasy game with a detailed story). <br>
<br>
I don't recall seeing the response after that (I may have it was a long time), and the boards were shut down not long after.  I wish I had a copy of that thread.  LOL. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uruss386.showPublicProfile?language=EN>russ386</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/30/01 2:14:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=935.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another TLC rant ... sigh ...</span><hr size=1> You know, TLC is sort of paradoxical.  I came to Firiona Vie for several things.  One, I dislike extreme twinks.  I kind of like the low-level scrimp and save, but that's just me.  Two, grouping and language restrictions.  My RP character dictates that I don't want to group with trolls, dark elves, and their ilk.  Three, the simple newness of the server.  Kind of interesting to see all of the guilds grow up and get to know lots of people from day one.  <br>
<br>
Now, I'm quite satisfied on all of these points.  Language restrictions are intresting, too, although kind of easy to get around.  I've had lots of interesting RP encounters, and made many good friends.  However, TLC and the low population are seriously bumming me out.  Bumming me out to the point where I started a bard on Vazaelle that I anticipate spending more and more time with, even though I have a fairly nice Level 30 Monk here.  <br>
<br>
How is TLC paradoxical?  Well, it is supposed to dissuade the power-gamers from farming low-level items to sell.  OK, it does do that.  But then don't many power-gamers have several accounts?  Couldn't I just buy another account, PL a character up to whatever level I need to be able to kill the mob, then give it to my main, who is able to take it because it isn't no-drop.  Hmm, sounds like a conspiracy to get us to buy more accounts doesn't it?  Makes you want to be a power-gamer doesn't it?  And don't even talk to me about the screwed-up economy on this server.  Personally, I say put NO DROP back on and take out TLC.  Let the farmers come.  I'll kill hill giants for money when I need it, thank you very much.  Then they can sit in their little camps farming and I'll be happy to buy their wares. <p>Tenzin Dralha <BR>
